               <head>Poem in praise of Navvab Ghaziuddin Haidar, Avadh/Oudh</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh98002075 http://lccn.loc.gov/n85018147 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008116463 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89002521" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16286-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Tarjī‘-band or stanzaic poem in praise of Ghāzī al-Dīn Ḥaydar, King of Awadh (reg. 1230-43/1814-27). The present manuscript was copied for the same patron, whose name appears in the colophon, preceded by with multiple laudatory epithets.</p>
                        <p>The poem comprises seven stanzas, each of which begins on a new page, with the Basmala, and closes with a couplet in a different rhyme from that of the stanza. The author of the poem is not named.</p>
                        <p>Begins:
Basmala  al-Salām ay sāya-at khwurshīd-i Rabb al-‘Ālamīn,
āsmān-i ‘izz va tamkīn āftāb-i dād va dīn,
Muftī-i har chār daftar Khwāja-’i har hasht jild,
Dāvar-i har shish jihat A‘ẓam Amīr al-Mu’minīn
</p>
                        <p>Ends:
Zāyirān-i Rawża āb-rā bar dar-i Khuld-i barīn,
mīrasad āvāz-i ṭibbam (sic, i.e. ṭablam?) fa-dhkhulūhā khālidīn
</p>
                        <p>Other contents: 1r and 28r, seal impressions of banda-’i Pādshāh Sharaf Ḥusayn and of Niẓām al-Mulk...al-Dawla...Nāṣir Ṭabāṭabā’ī.</p>
                        <p>Lucknow, 4th regnal year (1233-4/1817-18). Copied by Muḥammad Ibrāhīm. </p>
                        <p>Calligraphic nasta‘līq. 8 lines. All recto sides are blank. Text enclosed in cloudbands against lightly gilt folio with bright gilt squares at the beginning or end of each half-line. Simple gilt arabesques in margins. Leaves made of four thicknesses of soft beige paper. Damage from handling and small wormholes, chiefly in the margins, throughout. 28 folios. 315 x 200 mm.; text area 263 x 143 mm. Original red leather covers with gilt ornamentation in European style.</p>
                        <p>Purchased at Christie's South Kensington auction, 12 October 2006, Lot 605</p>
